{"id":14880859,"mediaExerciseId":"d4b09151-dc79-48b6-b411-1b4081ea59e6","exerciseName":"12","chapterName":"4","chapterTitle":"Long-Term Financial Planning and Growth","groupId":612285,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":119,"solutions":[{"id":5946351,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"The exercise will require us to compute the internal growth rate of A7X Co.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/bb93a18ae853816c5152c82982dceae9/d8f235e08304e0d86e6ab96584a96d0a/lateximg_large.png","width":993},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/bb93a18ae853816c5152c82982dceae9/d8f235e08304e0d86e6ab96584a96d0a/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"### Let's first provide the given data in the problem.\n\n* The ROA (return on assets) is 7.6%.\n* The payout ratio is 25%.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement.\n\n### Compute the internal growth rate.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"### Determine the retention ratio.\n\nThe given in the problem is the payout ratio. The retention ratio is the opposite of the payout ratio. \n\nThe formula is as follows.\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Retention Ratio}&= 1 - \\text{Payout ratio}\\\\[15pt]\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Therefore, the retention ratio is as follows.\n\nThe payout ratio of 25% is converted to the decimal value, which is 0.25.\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Retention Ratio}&= 1 - 0.25\\\\[15pt]\n&= 0.75 \\times 100\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{75\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\nTherefore, the retention ratio is **75%**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"### Compute the internal growth rate.\n\n**Internal Growth Rate** - It's one of the growth rates that a company can achieve without external support and financing.\n\n**Terms:**\n**ROA** - Return on assets.\n**b** - Retention ratio\n\nThe formula is as follows.\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Internal Growth Rate}&= \\dfrac{\\text{ROA $\\times$ b}}{1 - \\text{ROA $\\times$ b}}\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\dfrac{7.6\\% \\times 75\\%}{1-7.6\\% \\times 75\\%}\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\dfrac{0.057}{1 - 0.057}\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\dfrac{0.057}{0.943}\\\\[15pt]\n&=0.604  \\times 100\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\textbf{6.04\\%}} \n\n\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\nTherefore, the internal growth rate of AX7 Co. is **6.04%**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"26e1a0e3-6a46-470c-949a-8562adc21a05","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880860,"exerciseName":"13","page":119,"hasSolution":tr